-- Angolan President Names Central Bank Governor Economy Minister, Angop Says
-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 2010-10-05T05:41:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/angolan-president-names-central-bank-governor-economy-minister-angop-says.html
Angolan President  Jose Eduardo  dos
Santos appointed central bank Governor  Abraao Gourgel  as
minister of a newly created economy ministry,  Agencia Angola
Press  reported, citing the southern African nation’s leader.  The new entity replaces the ministry of state and economic
coordination, the Luanda-based news agency reported.  Manuel Nunes Junior , who headed the economic coordination ministry,
will be moved to another institution, Angop reported, without
naming the department. José de Lima Massano was named governor
of Banco Nacional de Angola, while Laura Maria Alcantara
Monteiro was fired as deputy central bank governor.  Sebastian Jose Antonio Martins was appointed interior
minister and General  Geraldo Sachipengo Nunda  will be head of
the armed forces, replacing Francisco Pereira Furtado, Angop
reported.  The economy ministry will formulate and evaluate state
business development and help improve efficiency in public
enterprises, while the finance ministry will regulate markets,
according to Angop.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Candido Mendes  in Luanda via Johannesburg at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 